## Available Skills (what the generated code can call)
- s.tap(locate("element description")) — tap on a UI element found by description
- s.swipe(x1, y1, x2, y2, duration_ms=300) — perform a swipe gesture
- s.input_text("text") — type text into the currently focused element
- s.press_key("BACK") / "ENTER" / "HOME" — press a hardware or system key
- s.launch_app("com.example.app") — launch an application by package/bundle ID
- locate("description") — find an element, returns an ElementMatch

## Rules
1. Each step must be ONE atomic UI action (tap / swipe / type / press key / launch app).
2. Steps must be in sequential execution order.
3. Do NOT include assertions as steps — they are handled separately.
4. Keep intent descriptions concise (≤20 words each).
5. rollback_hint should describe how to undo or recover from this step.
6. Return ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text.

